00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:59,532
[ Guys Chattering,
Laughing ]

223
00:15:02,302 --> 00:15:05,272
Oh, shit.
Oh, that's Mr. Thomas.

224
00:15:05,305 --> 00:15:07,507
The social studies
teacher?

225
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:10,177
[ Simon ]
Damn. That is him.

226
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:12,946
Man, even scholarly-type
motherfuckers gotta get
they smoke on.

227
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:17,384
[ Tristan ] Hey, that's why
that motherfucker's always
happy in class and shit.

228
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:20,120
[ Money ]
'Cause he was gettin' faded
in the teachers' lounge.

229
00:15:20,153 --> 00:15:22,990
[ Tristan Narrating ]
If you wanted weed, you
could go just about anywhere.

230
00:15:23,023 --> 00:15:25,058
I mean, there were plenty
of dealers out there...

231
00:15:25,092 --> 00:15:27,127
who would sell you
a nickel or a dime bag...

232
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:30,563
of just about whatever it was
you were into.

233
00:15:30,597 --> 00:15:35,035
But for variety
and that really good stuff...

234
00:15:35,068 --> 00:15:38,571
and for the dealer
who never ran out
of your favorite stash,

235
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:41,041
you had to go
to Sam's place.

236
00:15:41,074 --> 00:15:43,076
Yo, who's winning?
[ TV Playing ]

237
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:45,245
Sox. Last inning.
Rice just doubled.

238
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:49,582
Damn. Pee Wee must be
feelin' pretty good
let you come out after dark.

239
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:54,087
Usual?
Nah. He want four Thai sticks
and two ounces of the Buddha.

240
00:15:54,121 --> 00:15:55,555
All right.
You wait right here.
I'll be right back.

241
00:15:57,624 --> 00:16:00,693
And look, don't none of you
little motherfuckers
touch my food,

242
00:16:00,727 --> 00:16:03,596
especially you,
you little fat fucker.

243
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:06,066
Hey, fuck you.
Who the fuck
is he callin' fat?

244
00:16:06,099 --> 00:16:08,101
[ Money ]
Your fat ass.
[ Simon ] Fuck you.

245
00:16:15,142 --> 00:16:17,210
[ Man Groaning ]
[ Man #2 ]
What the fuck you--

246
00:16:17,244 --> 00:16:21,181
[ Groaning ]
Hey! What the fuck?
What's wrong with you?

247
00:16:21,214 --> 00:16:24,117
- Come on, guys.
Let's go.
- You ain't gonna pay?

248
00:16:24,151 --> 00:16:26,519
Man, sometimes you get on
my motherfuckin' nerve.

249
00:16:26,553 --> 00:16:28,655
How we gonna get outta here?
They're blockin' the door.
[ Commotion Continues ]

250
00:16:28,688 --> 00:16:31,024
Let's go out the back door.
[ Man ]
Goddamn!

251
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:33,293
Go! Go!
Get outta my house!

252
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:35,395
Take this shit outside!
What's wrong with you?

253
00:16:39,199 --> 00:16:41,434
Come on, E-Bone!
We gotta get goin'!

254
00:16:41,468 --> 00:16:43,670
Come on, man!
We gotta go!
We gotta go!

255
00:16:43,703 --> 00:16:45,438
Go, go, go!
Go, go!

256
00:16:52,179 --> 00:16:54,247
[ All Out Of Breath ]

257
00:16:54,281 --> 00:16:56,316
Hey, man, anybody comin'?

258
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:59,319
They prob-- They probably
don't even know
we left yet.

259
00:16:59,352 --> 00:17:01,521
How much shit
did you get?
Man, I don't know.

260
00:17:02,722 --> 00:17:06,126
Damn! We gonna get higher
than a motherfucker!

261
00:17:06,159 --> 00:17:08,061
Hell, yeah!
[ Laughing ]

262
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:11,531
What you trippin' on,
Tris?

263
00:17:14,201 --> 00:17:16,636
What if we didn't
smoke all of it?

264
00:17:16,669 --> 00:17:19,106
I know you ain't talkin'
about sellin' it.

265
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:22,275
Why not?
But where, man?

266
00:17:22,309 --> 00:17:25,145
Lathan and them got it
locked down from Gold Fall
to Four Corners.

267
00:17:25,178 --> 00:17:28,448
In case y'all don't remember,
that was Benny up in that
Cadillac this afternoon.

268
00:17:28,481 --> 00:17:31,151
And I ain't tryin'
to fuck with Benny, man.

269
00:17:31,184 --> 00:17:33,486
[ Tristan ]
Who said anything about
sellin' it on the streets?

270
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,788
We can sell it at school.

271
00:17:35,822 --> 00:17:39,726
All you got is a few burnouts
selling nickel bags
to they friends.

272
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:41,828
We'd be the only crew.

273
00:17:41,861 --> 00:17:44,364
We could supply the burnouts
and take they customers.

274
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:50,237
And that ain't even
the beautiful thing.
What's the beautiful thing?

275
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:53,506
[ School Bell Ringing ]
We don't have to worry
about gettin' caught...

276
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:55,775
'cause we gonna be
supplyin' the teachers.

277
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:57,877
[ Money ]
Ain't no teachers gonna
buy no herb, Tris.

278
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:01,114
Shit, man.
We just saw Mr. Thomas
buy from Sam today.

279
00:18:01,148 --> 00:18:04,384
Damn motherfuckin'
skippy. Shit.

280
00:18:04,417 --> 00:18:06,686
I'm with you, Tris.
E.

281
00:18:06,719 --> 00:18:09,389
Me too.
Let's do it.

282
00:18:09,422 --> 00:18:12,559
Let's do this.
Let's go.

283
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:15,328
[ Knocking ]

284
00:18:15,362 --> 00:18:18,265
[ Tristan Narrating ]
When we ran out of the stash
we ripped off from Sam,

285
00:18:18,298 --> 00:18:20,433
we started buying from him
to supply our customers.

286
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:24,504
Pee Wee squared it with Sam
about us stealin' from him,

287
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:26,906
so we let him get high
as much as he wants.

288
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:29,642
We were buying so much shit,
it didn't matter to us.

289
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:34,881
At first, we thought
the money was pretty good,

290
00:18:34,914 --> 00:18:37,217
but we had to kick
so much of it back to Sam...

291
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:40,920
that we realized
he was the one gettin' paid.

292
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:43,523
That's when I decided
to grow our own shit,

293
00:18:43,556 --> 00:18:46,693
and then the paper
came in nonstop.

294
00:18:46,726 --> 00:18:49,329
E-Bone got pretty good
at growin' that shit too.

295
00:18:49,362 --> 00:18:52,232
Twinkie helped us out
by lettin' us use
the back room...

296
00:18:52,265 --> 00:18:54,634
in one of his girls'
apartments.

297
00:18:54,667 --> 00:18:57,304
We kicked back
a couple hundred to her
every once in a while...

298
00:18:57,337 --> 00:18:59,806
for lettin' us
keep the place.

299
00:18:59,839 --> 00:19:03,743
She appreciated that
and let us know.

300
00:19:03,776 --> 00:19:05,612
We couldn't believe
the life we were livin'.

301
00:19:10,283 --> 00:19:12,652
Where you goin' E-Bone?
Where you goin', boy?

302
00:19:12,685 --> 00:19:14,821
That's some dope new gear
you sportin', E-Bone.

303
00:19:18,391 --> 00:19:20,427
- Get up, girl.
- What the fuck
y'all want?

304
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,895
You ain't so tough
without your crew,
huh, you little punk?

305
00:19:22,929 --> 00:19:25,698
I told Tristan I was
comin' back for my shit,
didn't I?

306
00:19:25,732 --> 00:19:27,934
I guess I'm just gonna
have to take it out
your ass, ain't I?

307
00:19:29,969 --> 00:19:31,638
[ Laughing ]

308
00:19:40,847 --> 00:19:43,250
We bombin' on all you
punk-ass bitches!

309
00:19:43,283 --> 00:19:44,917
This is our
motherfuckin' block!

310
00:19:44,951 --> 00:19:46,953
[ Kick Lands ]

311
00:19:57,597 --> 00:20:00,500
[ Door Opens, Closes ]
[ Tristan ]
Hey, Uncle Rob.

312
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:03,603
Hey, little Mack.
How you doin'?

313
00:20:03,636 --> 00:20:06,506
Good. Pretty good.
Hey. The place--

314
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:08,908
The place looks good.
[ Scoffs ]

315
00:20:08,941 --> 00:20:11,511
What this place
looks like is empty.

316
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:13,513
It ain't caught on
the way I thought
it would.

317
00:20:14,714 --> 00:20:16,649
[ Paper Rustling ]

318
00:20:18,485 --> 00:20:21,254
Boy, what are you doin'?

319
00:20:21,288 --> 00:20:23,290
It's the first of the month.

320
00:20:23,323 --> 00:20:25,992
Look, the rent on this place
ain't gonna pay itself.

321
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:28,395
The money don't know
where it comes from,
so just take it.

322
00:20:28,428 --> 00:20:31,798
Boy, if your daddy knew
what you was doin',
he'd kill you.

323
00:20:31,831 --> 00:20:35,435
And if he knew I was taking
money from you to run this
place, I'd be just as dead.

324
00:20:35,468 --> 00:20:37,670
But he doesn't know, and,
as long as he lives,

325
00:20:37,704 --> 00:20:40,840
he doesn't ever need
to know about this, right?

326
00:20:45,011 --> 00:20:47,947
Right.
The barbershop's
gonna pick up.

327
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:52,685
I know it will. I mean,
I believe in you, Uncle Rob.

328
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:54,521
What good is makin' money
if you can't do nothin'
with it?

329
00:20:54,554 --> 00:20:57,857
[ Sirens Wailing ]

330
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:00,793
You know, boy, sometimes
I think you the grown-up
and I'm the child.

331
00:21:00,827 --> 00:21:04,531
Now, uh, we gotta
get on home before
Mama's dinner gets cold.

332
00:21:06,466 --> 00:21:08,635
Hey, Tristan, hold up.
There's somethin'...

333
00:21:08,668 --> 00:21:10,970
I been wantin'
to talk to you about
for a long while now.

334
00:21:11,003 --> 00:21:13,340
I really gotta go, Uncle--
Don't you interrupt me.

335
00:21:13,373 --> 00:21:16,543
Now, if you gonna
be in this game--

336
00:21:16,576 --> 00:21:19,779
and from the looks of things,
it looks like you done made up
your mind about that--

337
00:21:19,812 --> 00:21:23,383
you got to realize
that this is a losin' game.

338
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:26,886
Drug dealers don't have
pensions, they don't end up
with retirement funds...

339
00:21:26,919 --> 00:21:29,088
and they don't end up
with the big house
on the hill.

340
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:32,659
They end up dead
or wishin'
that they were.

341
00:21:32,692 --> 00:21:36,429
So, what's your point, Unc?
Make a plan.
That's the point.

342
00:21:36,463 --> 00:21:39,466
Do somethin'
with your money.

343
00:21:39,499 --> 00:21:42,902
Set yourself up
to get out of this game
when the time is right.

344
00:21:42,935 --> 00:21:45,037
I'm talkin' about
investments--

345
00:21:45,071 --> 00:21:47,374
legitimate investments.

346
00:21:47,407 --> 00:21:49,576
Now, I'm gonna
take this money
as an investment.

347
00:21:49,609 --> 00:21:53,012
You investin'
in my barbershop.

348
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:56,383
I'm gonna teach you
the ins and outs
of this business.

349
00:21:56,416 --> 00:21:59,786
From now on,
we not just relatives,
we are partners.

350
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:02,355
And we gonna make this
a success together.

351
00:22:04,391 --> 00:22:06,092
Partners.
Partners.

352
00:22:09,496 --> 00:22:12,632
All right.
You tell your mama
I'm gonna be a little late.

353
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:14,501
All right.
Y'all go on
and eat without me.

354
00:22:14,534 --> 00:22:16,903
All right.
[ Laughs ]

355
00:22:16,936 --> 00:22:20,039
[ Woman ]
Baby, you haven't eaten
your mashed potatoes.

356
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:22,141
[ Girl ]
I don't like them.

357
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,544
But they'll make you
big and strong.

358
00:22:24,577 --> 00:22:26,946
You've been saying that
for years, Mom.

359
00:22:26,979 --> 00:22:29,749
[ Laughs ]
What do you know about
"years," little girl?

360
00:22:29,782 --> 00:22:32,519
You only eight.
Yeah, but I'm
an old soul.

361
00:22:32,552 --> 00:22:34,954
[ All Laugh ]

362
00:22:34,987 --> 00:22:37,590
"Old soul."

363
00:22:37,624 --> 00:22:38,991
How's everything
with you, Tristan?

364
00:22:39,025 --> 00:22:41,628
Good, Pops.
Honey?

365
00:22:41,661 --> 00:22:45,465
Have you told Tristan
you saw his report card?

366
00:22:45,498 --> 00:22:49,469
No, I didn't.
Straight A's again, huh?

367
00:22:49,502 --> 00:22:52,539
You keep this up, we gonna
have to send you to Harvard.
[ Knocking ]

368
00:22:52,572 --> 00:22:55,107
- I'll get it.
- I'll get it.
You help your mother.

369
00:22:58,778 --> 00:23:01,448
Tristan.
Simon and Marlon
are here.

370
00:23:03,950 --> 00:23:07,053
Wass-- Wassup, man?
What y'all doin' here?
You-- You want some chicken?

371
00:23:09,656 --> 00:23:13,059
- We got a problem, man.
- What's up?

372
00:23:13,092 --> 00:23:15,628
It's E-Bone.

373
00:23:19,799 --> 00:23:21,601
[ Knocking ]

374
00:23:26,706 --> 00:23:30,843
Tristan, Simon, Money.
Broke-ass
Pee Wee.

375
00:23:30,877 --> 00:23:32,912
Someone try to break
your legs too?

376
00:23:32,945 --> 00:23:35,047
Took you guys
long enough to get here.
Shut your ass.

377
00:23:35,081 --> 00:23:37,450
Can we see him?

378
00:23:37,484 --> 00:23:39,486
Come on in.

379
00:23:41,153 --> 00:23:43,155
[ Sniffs ]

380
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:49,962
- Hey. What up, fellas?
- What up, E?

381
00:23:49,996 --> 00:23:52,899
What's the deal, E?
How you feelin',
killer?

382
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:56,068
Come on, now.
Edward, I want you
to finish this.

383
00:23:56,102 --> 00:23:59,572
Look, Nana, I need
to talk to my friends.

384
00:23:59,606 --> 00:24:02,709
I'm not going anywhere
until you finish eating.

385
00:24:02,742 --> 00:24:05,211
It's okay, Mrs. Winslett.
I'll make sure he eats it.

386
00:24:05,244 --> 00:24:08,715
I'll make sure
he eats it all.

387
00:24:08,748 --> 00:24:11,584
- Is that all right
with you, Edward?
- Yes, Nana.

388
00:24:11,618 --> 00:24:14,020
I'll be outside
if you need me.

389
00:24:14,053 --> 00:24:16,623
Okay.

390
00:24:22,995 --> 00:24:25,932
Make sure he eats
all of it, Tristan.

391
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:28,735
Yeah. Make sure
he gets it
and not Simon.

392
00:24:33,205 --> 00:24:36,943
- I ain't gonna feed ya.
- [ Bowl Clatters ]

393
00:24:36,976 --> 00:24:40,547
- So, do you feel
as bad as you look?
- What took y'all so long?

394
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:42,549
Yo, it was Lathan and them,
wasn't it?

395
00:24:42,582 --> 00:24:44,984
Yeah.
[ Money ] Yo, it don't
make sense, E--

396
00:24:45,017 --> 00:24:47,754
him fucking you up like this
over a couple of ounces?

397
00:24:47,787 --> 00:24:51,558
Three months ago?
It ain't makin' sense, E.

398
00:24:51,591 --> 00:24:53,626
[ Simon ]
Hey, what you
talkin' about, man?

399
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:57,764
We straight embarrassed him,
in front of Benny too.

400
00:24:57,797 --> 00:25:00,232
[ Scoffs ]
I say you got lucky, E.

401
00:25:00,266 --> 00:25:02,802
He might have killed your ass.

402
00:25:02,835 --> 00:25:06,038
- Look, what happened, E-Bone?
- What you mean,
"What happened?"

403
00:25:06,072 --> 00:25:08,007
I got fucked up.
That's what happened.

404
00:25:09,108 --> 00:25:11,544
Look, Money's right.

405
00:25:11,578 --> 00:25:14,080
Lathan wouldn't have
came after you like this
over a couple ounces.

406
00:25:14,113 --> 00:25:16,115
Yeah. Come on, E.
[ Tristan ]
Too much time has passed.

407
00:25:16,148 --> 00:25:18,885
So, what happened?

408
00:25:18,918 --> 00:25:21,287
Look, I was doin' business
on the street.

409
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:23,322
[ Scoffs ]
You bullshittin'.

410
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:27,059
- We said only at school.
- Man, I know
what we said.

411
00:25:27,093 --> 00:25:28,928
But there's money
on the street, kid.
I'm telling you.

412
00:25:28,961 --> 00:25:32,732
So, in other words, you almost
get killed for a few pennies.

413
00:25:32,765 --> 00:25:35,835
Man, is you stupid?
Pennies?

414
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:38,270
Money, go over there and
bring me that jar of peanuts.

415
00:25:45,244 --> 00:25:47,246
Oh, shit.

416
00:25:52,284 --> 00:25:54,286
Man, let me help you.

417
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:05,998
Yeah, and this is only
from me working
just three weeks.

418
00:26:06,032 --> 00:26:09,602
Man, imagine all of us
working, man, for months
or even years.

419
00:26:09,636 --> 00:26:12,304
Just think of all the shit
we can get, Tris.

420
00:26:12,338 --> 00:26:15,174
Yo, what about Lathan?
We still gotta deal
with him.

421
00:26:15,207 --> 00:26:17,677
Man, fuck Lathan, man.

422
00:26:19,712 --> 00:26:21,748
Look.

423
00:26:21,781 --> 00:26:23,983
Hey, where the fuck
you get that, man?

424
00:26:24,016 --> 00:26:27,820
Dennis and his brother Randy
robbed a gun store in Brockton
a couple days ago.

425
00:26:27,854 --> 00:26:31,924
They got all kinds of steel.
We can get anything we want.

426
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,762
Let's go, fellas.

427
00:26:39,231 --> 00:26:41,233
Get better, man.

428
00:26:43,135 --> 00:26:45,404
Hey, I want y'all
to know somethin'.

429
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:48,174
I wasn't holdin' out on y'all.
I was gonna tell you.

430
00:26:50,309 --> 00:26:53,946
I just wanted to see
what was out there
on the street, you know?

431
00:26:56,315 --> 00:26:58,885
Yeah, man.
Yeah, man.
We know.

432
00:26:58,918 --> 00:27:00,953
Get better.
Take care of that eye.

433
00:27:00,987 --> 00:27:02,889
Holler at you
in a minute.

434
00:27:11,097 --> 00:27:14,901
[ School Bell Rings ]

435
00:27:14,934 --> 00:27:17,236
[ Chattering ]

436
00:27:21,874 --> 00:27:24,711
- [ Both ] Hi, Tristan.
- Hey, wassup?

437
00:27:27,246 --> 00:27:30,082
Oh, shit.
You're not
gonna speak?

438
00:27:30,116 --> 00:27:33,252
You talkin' to me?
I ain't talkin'
to myself.

439
00:27:33,285 --> 00:27:36,355
I don't think
I remember your name.
You gonna do me like that.

440
00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:40,827
You're cute and everything,
and I know you got this
little mack thing goin' on,

441
00:27:40,860 --> 00:27:42,895
but I can't be messin'
with no drug dealers.

442
00:27:42,929 --> 00:27:45,231
I ain't no drug dealer.
Come on, Tristan.
I'm not stupid.

443
00:27:45,264 --> 00:27:47,767
So you do remember
my name.

444
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:51,938
Okay, so maybe I do,
but that doesn't change
the fact that you're--

445
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:56,042
What's that?
Open it.

446
00:28:00,747 --> 00:28:03,449
It's beautiful.
It's yours.

447
00:28:03,482 --> 00:28:09,188
I can't take this.
You have to.
It's nonrefundable.

448
00:28:09,221 --> 00:28:14,193
Listen, I hear you on this
little drug-dealing thing
you're talkin' about, right?

449
00:28:14,226 --> 00:28:17,396
But I ain't no dealer.
I just help out my friends
from time to time.

450
00:28:17,429 --> 00:28:20,299
That's all?
That's all.
I promise.

451
00:28:22,101 --> 00:28:24,136
Thanks for the necklace.

452
00:28:24,170 --> 00:28:26,272
So can I
walk you home?

453
00:28:26,305 --> 00:28:30,076
Okay.
You look beautiful
with that.

454
00:28:30,109 --> 00:28:33,345
[ Tristan ]
You sure they in there?
[ E-Bone ] That's the word.

455
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:36,315
Let's do this.

456
00:28:36,348 --> 00:28:40,486
[ Tristan Narrating ]
I wasn't content with what
we had just dealin' at school.

457
00:28:41,988 --> 00:28:45,491
E-Bone kicked off
the inevitable.

458
00:28:45,524 --> 00:28:49,328
First rule of business--
control the market.

459
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:52,899
It was time
to elevate the game.

460
00:28:52,932 --> 00:28:55,201
Shit. How many books
y'all get?

461
00:28:55,234 --> 00:28:58,237
Y'all count 'em up.
I gotta take a piss.

462
00:28:59,505 --> 00:29:01,808
Lathan be cheatin'.
When he comes back,

463
00:29:01,841 --> 00:29:03,943
I'm gonna put
a bullet in his ass.

464
00:29:03,976 --> 00:29:06,946
That's why I don't like
playin' with him,
'cause he always be cheatin'.

465
00:29:06,979 --> 00:29:08,480
** [ Rap, Indistinct ]

466
00:29:18,925 --> 00:29:20,960
[ Grunts ]

467
00:29:20,993 --> 00:29:22,795
[ Gunfire Continues ]

468
00:29:33,039 --> 00:29:37,143
Aw, shit! What the fuck
you goin' to do, bitch?

469
00:29:37,176 --> 00:29:40,179
Huh, little Tristan?
[ Laughing ]

470
00:29:40,212 --> 00:29:43,082
You better kill my ass
right now, motherfucker,

471
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:45,351
if you got the balls,
bitch.

472
00:29:48,187 --> 00:29:51,357
[ Gasping ]
Mother--

473
00:29:51,390 --> 00:29:54,193
[ Tristan Narrating ]
I read this book about
World War II one time.

474
00:29:54,226 --> 00:29:56,362
Damn.
One of the soldiers said that
every time he killed someone,

475
00:29:56,395 --> 00:29:59,565
he saw the face
of the first man he murdered.

476
00:29:59,598 --> 00:30:02,101
It's like none of
the other faces register.

477
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:04,837
You kept killin' the same guy
over and over again.
[ Gasps ] Mama.

478
00:30:10,009 --> 00:30:12,078
Lathan was the first cat
I ever killed.

479
00:30:12,111 --> 00:30:14,613
The soldier was right.

480
00:30:14,646 --> 00:30:17,449
I killed other dudes,

481
00:30:17,483 --> 00:30:20,552
but, to this day,
I can only see Lathan's face,

482
00:30:20,586 --> 00:30:23,890
knowin'--
Come on, Tris.
Let's go, man.

483
00:30:23,923 --> 00:30:25,958
knowin' he was gonna die.

484
00:30:25,992 --> 00:30:29,228
Come on, man.
Let's go.
In less than a second,

485
00:30:29,261 --> 00:30:31,864
what little bit of childhood
we had left was gone.

486
00:30:31,898 --> 00:30:35,134
I had made decisions
about my life based on
my friendships with my boys,

487
00:30:35,167 --> 00:30:38,370
but, until that moment,
I could always walk away.

488
00:30:38,404 --> 00:30:41,540
Now there was no
walkin' away.
Lathan!

489
00:30:41,573 --> 00:30:45,444
I was no longer a kid.
Now I was a gangster.

490
00:30:45,477 --> 00:30:49,015
We all were, and that's
the way we wanted it.

491
00:30:49,048 --> 00:30:51,083
Weed is
a pretty lightweight drug,

492
00:30:51,117 --> 00:30:53,352
even back then.

493
00:30:53,385 --> 00:30:57,656
In that game, you usually
ain't got to worry about
no one tryin' to murder you.

494
00:30:57,689 --> 00:31:00,927
I killed Lathan because
he was becomin' a pain,

495
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:04,030
and I knew
I would feel better
once he was gone.

496
00:31:04,063 --> 00:31:07,934
Now everyone had no choice
but to take us seriously.

497
00:31:07,967 --> 00:31:10,269
But I had to keep
telling myself over and over,

498
00:31:10,302 --> 00:31:13,039
it was just business.

499
00:31:13,072 --> 00:31:16,342
I said it enough times
that I actually
started to believe it.

500
00:31:16,375 --> 00:31:18,510
There wasn't any reason
to kill the rest of 'em.

501
00:31:18,544 --> 00:31:21,613
Without Lathan,
they were nothin'.

502
00:31:21,647 --> 00:31:24,450
And no one goes to the cops
in this neighborhood.

503
00:31:28,154 --> 00:31:30,389
Things were different now.

504
00:31:30,422 --> 00:31:33,125
We were ghetto superstars
before, but,

505
00:31:33,159 --> 00:31:36,228
after we took out Lathan
and took over all his customers,

506
00:31:37,329 --> 00:31:39,498
now we were ghetto legends.

507
00:31:44,436 --> 00:31:46,638
But there was one face...

508
00:31:46,672 --> 00:31:49,241
that didn't show a look
of admiration or respect.

509
00:31:49,275 --> 00:31:51,944
[ School Bell Rings ]

510
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:23,275
* These are the days
of our lives
that we're livin' *

511
00:32:23,309 --> 00:32:28,981
* We're livin' the days
of our deadliest sins *
You motherfuckers sit down.

512
00:32:29,015 --> 00:32:30,682
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]
You know why you're here?

513
00:32:30,716 --> 00:32:32,751
No.

514
00:32:32,784 --> 00:32:36,488
- You know who I am though?
- Yeah, we know.

515
00:32:45,231 --> 00:32:48,334
- What's that?
- It's new business.

516
00:32:48,367 --> 00:32:50,669
It's your new business.

517
00:32:50,702 --> 00:32:53,139
We doin' pretty good
with the one we got.

518
00:32:53,172 --> 00:32:56,042
- [ Laughing ]
- Boy, you ain't doin' shit.

519
00:32:56,075 --> 00:33:00,212
You take your best day
and you times it by 10,

520
00:33:00,246 --> 00:33:04,216
and it's your worst day ever
selling this shit right here.

521
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:06,285
Word?
You like that, huh?

522
00:33:06,318 --> 00:33:09,488
Huh!
You like the sound of that?

523
00:33:09,521 --> 00:33:11,657
Well, if it's so good,
why you givin' it to us?

524
00:33:11,690 --> 00:33:14,193
Why not just give it to one
of your old crews?

525
00:33:14,226 --> 00:33:17,563
You must be Tristan.

526
00:33:19,431 --> 00:33:21,800
Yeah, that's me.
[ Sniffs ]

527
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:24,203
'Cause I like you, Tristan.

528
00:33:24,236 --> 00:33:26,605
I been watchin' you.

529
00:33:26,638 --> 00:33:29,007
You really handle business
very well.

530
00:33:30,209 --> 00:33:32,678
Besides, you owe me.

531
00:33:32,711 --> 00:33:35,381
How you figure that?

532
00:33:35,414 --> 00:33:38,584
You took out one of my crews,
but you didn't bother
to get permission.

533
00:33:38,617 --> 00:33:40,686
Now make no mistake.

534
00:33:40,719 --> 00:33:45,691
Now, this is not a demand.
It's a request.

535
00:33:45,724 --> 00:33:48,660
Shit, motherfuckers,
I ain't gonna beg y'all
to make this money.

536
00:33:48,694 --> 00:33:53,532
- What is it?
- It's a form of cocaine.

537
00:33:53,565 --> 00:33:57,369
Don't worry, little man.
We can teach you
how to cook that up.

538
00:33:57,403 --> 00:34:00,806
- [ Tristan ]
What do you call it?
- It's called "crack."

539
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:06,245
[ Tristan Narrating ]
And that was the beginning.

540
00:34:06,278 --> 00:34:08,447
* Bitch, what is it
Cross over *

541
00:34:11,617 --> 00:34:14,453
And this, this is the end.

542
00:34:14,486 --> 00:34:17,156
* You never seen 'em
drop like this
and lock they ass up *

543
00:34:17,189 --> 00:34:20,259
* Make it hot like this
and still don't
spill my drink *

544
00:34:20,292 --> 00:34:23,829
* My shit real on these streets
Feel my love for concrete **

545
00:34:23,862 --> 00:34:26,365
Brian Torrance
and Archie Tyler.

546
00:34:28,234 --> 00:34:30,336
They were detectives
assigned to our case.

547
00:34:30,369 --> 00:34:33,205
See, after 12 years,
the local cops
couldn't catch us,

548
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:35,407
so the brass assigned
Abbott and Costello here...
[ Chattering ]

549
00:34:35,441 --> 00:34:37,643
to make their presence known,

550
00:34:37,676 --> 00:34:40,879
thinkin' that,
if the heat was on,
we'd slow down a little,

551
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:43,382
maybe make a mistake
so they could catch us.

552
00:34:43,415 --> 00:34:45,817
As usual, they were wrong.

553
00:34:45,851 --> 00:34:49,655
How about it, Tris?
Any idea why somebody'd
come in here, rob your uncle?

554
00:34:49,688 --> 00:34:52,424
No, man.

555
00:34:52,458 --> 00:34:56,495
- No idea whatsoever, huh?
- That's what I just said.

556
00:34:56,528 --> 00:34:58,764
Well, why is it that I
don't believe you?

557
00:35:00,766 --> 00:35:03,702
I don't know.

558
00:35:03,735 --> 00:35:06,772
Maybe you
just a naturally
suspicious kinda guy.

559
00:35:06,805 --> 00:35:09,241
Let me ask you
a question.

560
00:35:09,275 --> 00:35:12,478
Why would they send
two vice detectives
to investigate a robbery?

561
00:35:12,511 --> 00:35:15,214
Fourteen-Paul--
drug-related theft.

562
00:35:17,849 --> 00:35:20,286
And what makes you think
it's drug-related?

563
00:35:20,319 --> 00:35:22,354
[ Detective ]
Oh, I don't know.

564
00:35:22,388 --> 00:35:25,591
Maybe because the owner
is a drug dealer.

565
00:35:25,624 --> 00:35:28,827
Whatever, man.
So, what happened,
Tris?

566
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:31,430
One of your little
crackhead buddies
get all mad at ya?

567
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:36,502
[ Scoffs ] If you two
wasn't so damn pathetic,

568
00:35:36,535 --> 00:35:38,837
you'd almost be funny.

569
00:35:38,870 --> 00:35:41,773
But instead, you're nothin'.

570
00:35:43,209 --> 00:35:45,544
Oh, I'm nothin', huh?

571
00:35:45,577 --> 00:35:47,913
You got no idea
how close we are, fucko!

572
00:35:47,946 --> 00:35:50,449
You and your little crew
are done.

573
00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:52,884
I guess that means you won't
be searchin' too hard
for the guy that robbed us.

574
00:35:52,918 --> 00:35:55,454
Now, will you?
Hey, Tris.

575
00:35:55,487 --> 00:35:57,523
If I was you,
[ Chuckles ]

576
00:35:57,556 --> 00:35:59,825
the shop would be
the last thing
I'd be worried about.

577
00:35:59,858 --> 00:36:03,329
You better start
growin' yourself some eyes
in the back of your head.

578
00:36:07,833 --> 00:36:10,569
[ Door Opens ]

579
00:36:16,575 --> 00:36:18,610
[ Tristan ]
What the fuck
were they doin' in here?

580
00:36:18,644 --> 00:36:20,812
Hey, I didn't call them.
They just showed up.

581
00:36:20,846 --> 00:36:22,881
Kinda like fungus.
[ Chuckling ]

582
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:24,950
It ain't funny, Unc.

583
00:36:24,983 --> 00:36:27,219
Torrance and Tyler
have it in for me.
You know that.

584
00:36:27,253 --> 00:36:28,987
I told you not to talk
to them clowns.

585
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:31,257
I didn't call them,

586
00:36:31,290 --> 00:36:32,891
and I didn't tell them
anything, Tristan.

587
00:36:34,893 --> 00:36:37,363
Look, I'm not one of them
little punks on the street.

588
00:36:37,396 --> 00:36:41,233
So do me a favor--
don't talk to me
like I am.

589
00:36:43,802 --> 00:36:45,604
[ Sighs ]

590
00:36:48,374 --> 00:36:50,376
I'm sorry, Unc.

591
00:36:51,543 --> 00:36:53,579
How much did they get
anyway?

592
00:36:53,612 --> 00:36:57,349
Couple hundred dollars
out of the register.

593
00:36:57,383 --> 00:36:59,885
Couldn't open the safe.

594
00:36:59,918 --> 00:37:03,689
Why don't you put bars
on the windows and doors like
everybody else on this street?

595
00:37:03,722 --> 00:37:06,392
I've been livin' and workin'
in this neighborhood
all my life.

596
00:37:06,425 --> 00:37:09,995
I ain't never had
no bars on the window.
I ain't about to start now.

597
00:37:10,028 --> 00:37:13,532
Times change.
You got that right.

598
00:37:13,565 --> 00:37:15,601
Twelve-year-olds
killin' each other.

599
00:37:15,634 --> 00:37:19,271
Goddamn psychopaths
everywhere you look.

600
00:37:19,305 --> 00:37:22,341
Look, I just came by
to make a bank run anyway.

601
00:37:22,374 --> 00:37:24,042
How much we got
to deposit?

602
00:37:24,075 --> 00:37:26,412
About four grand.

603
00:37:32,318 --> 00:37:35,421
Cool.
Be safe.

604
00:37:35,454 --> 00:37:37,489
I will.

605
00:37:37,523 --> 00:37:39,758
Hey, look, Unc, um,

606
00:37:39,791 --> 00:37:42,328
I'm sorry I snapped
at you earlier.
I didn't mean it.

607
00:37:42,361 --> 00:37:44,396
That's okay, Tristan.

608
00:37:46,665 --> 00:37:49,835
But you see what
I'm talkin' about, right?
What?

609
00:37:49,868 --> 00:37:52,971
About the neighborhood.
Yeah. How things change.
Yeah, I heard you.

610
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:56,908
No, not just how
things have changed,
but w they've changed.

611
00:37:56,942 --> 00:37:58,977
Have you asked yourself
that question?

612
00:37:59,010 --> 00:38:03,081
Come on, Unc.
Things change.
Times are hard.

613
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:05,451
No. There's more to it
than that.

614
00:38:05,484 --> 00:38:09,020
If you got somethin'
you wanna say to me, just
go ahead and say it, Uncle Rob.

615
00:38:09,054 --> 00:38:11,623
Look, it's the rock,
Tristan.

616
00:38:11,657 --> 00:38:13,792
Rock has fucked
this neighborhood up.

617
00:38:13,825 --> 00:38:17,529
No. Think about it.
There's junkies everywhere.

618
00:38:17,563 --> 00:38:19,598
It never used
to be like that.

619
00:38:19,631 --> 00:38:22,368
Crack has got these people
so wrapped up,
they're willin' to--

620
00:38:22,401 --> 00:38:25,103
to rob, to-to maim,
to kill anybody...

621
00:38:25,136 --> 00:38:27,473
just to get enough money
to get their next high.

622
00:38:27,506 --> 00:38:29,741
It was a crackhead
who broke in here.

623
00:38:29,775 --> 00:38:34,346
You don't know that.
Tristan, you got
a reputation.

624
00:38:34,380 --> 00:38:36,448
You got a reputation
for murderin' people.

625
00:38:36,482 --> 00:38:38,717
Now, what motherfuck
in his right mind...

626
00:38:38,750 --> 00:38:41,019
is gonna risk robbin' this place
so you can find out
who they are?

627
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:44,823
You, E-Bone, Simon and Money,
you might as well be
the motherfuckin' mob.

628
00:38:44,856 --> 00:38:48,093
Who's gonna go up against that
for a couple hundred dollars
and some change?

629
00:38:48,126 --> 00:38:51,329
So some motherfuckin' crackhead
came in here and robbed us?
That's just one case.

630
00:38:52,931 --> 00:38:55,534
You don't believe that,
and I know you don't.

631
00:38:57,403 --> 00:39:01,039
You don't wanna take
responsibility, but,
hey, I can understand.

632
00:39:01,072 --> 00:39:03,809
Now you wanna blame me
for all the fucked-up shit
in Boston?

633
00:39:03,842 --> 00:39:08,046
Crack is the problem,
and you're the biggest
crack dealer in the Sound End.

634
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:11,383
Fuck you, old man.

635
00:39:22,027 --> 00:39:24,396
God!
[ Tristan Narrating ]
We set up crack houses...

636
00:39:24,430 --> 00:39:26,665
all over the South End.

637
00:39:26,698 --> 00:39:29,167
Blue Hill and Intervale
was where we made
the bulk of our money.

638
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:32,070
If you wanted cocaine,
you didn't come to us.

639
00:39:32,103 --> 00:39:34,873
You just phoned it in,
and we came to you.

640
00:39:34,906 --> 00:39:39,010
E-Bone did most of the cooking.
He cooked up to eight keys a day
without fail.

641
00:39:39,044 --> 00:39:42,080
Then we asked someone
from the neighborhood
we thought we could trust...

642
00:39:42,113 --> 00:39:45,517
to make sure
that everything stayed stocked
and kept track of the weight.

643
00:39:45,551 --> 00:39:47,586
In the Blue Hill Ave house,
that was Buzz.

644
00:39:47,619 --> 00:39:51,089
Maceo chopped the keys
and broke them down into ounces.

645
00:39:51,122 --> 00:39:55,093
He added the benzocaine,
the procaine or vitamin B
to the weight that was chopped.

646
00:39:55,126 --> 00:39:58,430
Day-Day would take the orders
over the phone, always in code,

647
00:39:58,464 --> 00:40:00,866
so no one listenin'
would know what was
really goin' on.

648
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:02,934
And then he'd hand
each one of them
to the runners...

649
00:40:02,968 --> 00:40:06,538
along with a package
of what was ordered.

650
00:40:06,572 --> 00:40:10,742
Simon ran the house though.
In fact, he ran
all the houses we had.

651
00:40:10,776 --> 00:40:12,611
'Cause it didn't matter
how bad you were,

652
00:40:12,644 --> 00:40:14,713
nobody fucked with Simon.

653
00:40:14,746 --> 00:40:16,948
Nobody.
[ Money ] Word.

654
00:40:16,982 --> 00:40:20,018
When Money wasn't gettin' laid,
he kept everyone in line.

655
00:40:20,051 --> 00:40:22,921
If anything went wrong, Marlon
was the first to know about it.
[ Glass Shatters ]

656
00:40:22,954 --> 00:40:26,024
Most of the time,
the problem was handled
before I even knew about it.

657
00:40:26,057 --> 00:40:28,727
Hey, what the fuck
is all that noise
out there, man?

658
00:40:48,179 --> 00:40:50,181
[ Sighs ]

659
00:40:53,151 --> 00:40:56,755
Hey, baby.
Hey.

660
00:40:56,788 --> 00:41:00,158
You okay?
Why wouldn't I be?

661
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:04,462
'Cause you sittin' in here
in the dark.
[ Laughing]

662
00:41:13,905 --> 00:41:15,941
So.
What?

663
00:41:15,974 --> 00:41:17,976
What's goin' on?

664
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:24,482
Remember that?
[ Laughing ]

665
00:41:25,851 --> 00:41:28,954
Oh, man. Where'd you
get this thing?

666
00:41:28,987 --> 00:41:30,822
I found it at the bottom
of my jewelry box.

667
00:41:33,124 --> 00:41:35,861
That thing is ugly.
