00:54:48,653 --> 00:54:50,488
All right.

893
00:54:50,521 --> 00:54:52,723
So I'll get with you
tomorrow, right?

894
00:54:54,525 --> 00:54:56,527
Go on.

895
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:08,373
[ Gasps, Panting ]

896
00:55:16,080 --> 00:55:18,816
- [ Tristan ]
Wassup?
- Wassup, yo?

897
00:55:18,849 --> 00:55:21,519
Where's everybody else?

898
00:55:21,552 --> 00:55:23,721
They didn't show.

899
00:55:23,754 --> 00:55:26,924
Shit.
Everything's
gonna be cool.

900
00:55:26,957 --> 00:55:30,528
Long as me and you
stick together,
it's gonna be a'ight.

901
00:55:31,996 --> 00:55:34,565
Look, I threw out
all the hype...

902
00:55:34,599 --> 00:55:37,835
and had Buzz and them
board up the place.

903
00:55:37,868 --> 00:55:39,604
That oughta convince Benny
that we really shut it down.

904
00:55:44,975 --> 00:55:47,878
You ready for this, man?
'Cause it's gonna get ugly.

905
00:55:47,912 --> 00:55:50,915
We ain't got no choice.
Quittin' ain't an option.

906
00:55:50,948 --> 00:55:52,983
Besides, E-Bone was right.

907
00:55:53,017 --> 00:55:55,920
With Benny gone,
we'll get a better price.

908
00:55:56,987 --> 00:55:59,424
Yeah.

909
00:55:59,457 --> 00:56:01,692
Get everybody together
tonight.

910
00:56:01,726 --> 00:56:03,494
Figure out the best way
to do this thing.

911
00:56:03,528 --> 00:56:06,464
A'ight?
I'll see you tonight.

912
00:56:09,834 --> 00:56:12,503
Hey, yo, Tris.
Yeah.

913
00:56:14,739 --> 00:56:16,907
[ Inhales ]
You know, somewhere
in the back of my mind,

914
00:56:16,941 --> 00:56:19,109
I knew one day
it would come to this--

915
00:56:19,143 --> 00:56:21,679
a beat-down
between us and Benny.

916
00:56:21,712 --> 00:56:24,148
[ Chuckles ]
It's like we were
meant to do that shit.

917
00:56:24,181 --> 00:56:27,084
- I feel you, yo.
- Like that car
that night.

918
00:56:29,654 --> 00:56:33,458
After 12 years, man,
you still can't
get over that thing?

919
00:56:33,491 --> 00:56:35,660
Somethin'
about that car, dawg.

920
00:56:35,693 --> 00:56:39,664
- What?
- You don't think
I'm stupid?

921
00:56:39,697 --> 00:56:42,733
[ Thunder Crashes ]
Man, just say what the fuck
is on your mind.

922
00:56:42,767 --> 00:56:47,104
You know, part of me feel
like I was supposed to get
hit by that car that night.

923
00:56:47,137 --> 00:56:50,875
It's like every second
that I've lived after that
has been borrowed time.

924
00:56:50,908 --> 00:56:53,844
[ Laughs ]
That's why
shit don't scare me.

925
00:56:53,878 --> 00:56:57,582
'Cause maybe I ain't
supposed to be here anyway.
What do you think?

926
00:56:57,615 --> 00:56:59,717
What do I think?

927
00:56:59,750 --> 00:57:03,688
I think thinkin'
is the problem.

928
00:57:03,721 --> 00:57:07,925
You thinkin' too much.
Let me do the thinkin',
all right?

929
00:57:07,958 --> 00:57:10,895
- What you sayin', I'm stupid?
- No. Hell, no.
I ain't sayin' you stupid.

930
00:57:10,928 --> 00:57:12,897
I can't have no
stupid motherfuckers
watchin' my back.

931
00:57:12,930 --> 00:57:15,533
But you didn't get hit
by that car that night.

932
00:57:15,566 --> 00:57:18,202
It missed you,
and that's that.

933
00:57:18,235 --> 00:57:22,239
- That's 'cause you was
lookin' out, dawg.
- Whatever, man.

934
00:57:22,272 --> 00:57:25,476
The point is, as far as
livin' on borrowed time,

935
00:57:25,510 --> 00:57:27,478
we all might be one step
away from the grave.

936
00:57:28,746 --> 00:57:33,684
All we gotta do...
is handle business,

937
00:57:33,718 --> 00:57:36,954
and everything gonna be
all right, a'ight?

938
00:57:39,023 --> 00:57:42,493
- All right, yo.
- Watch out! Watch out!
[ Laughing ]

939
00:57:42,527 --> 00:57:44,929
[ Simon's Voice ]
What's he plan on doin'?

940
00:57:44,962 --> 00:57:48,032
[ Tristan's Voice ]
Takin' us out.
He just needs an excuse.

941
00:57:48,065 --> 00:57:50,501
[ E-Bone's Voice ]
I knew I should've peeled
this cap right then and there.

942
00:57:50,535 --> 00:57:53,971
[ Machine Clicks Off ]
Well, well.

943
00:57:54,004 --> 00:57:57,642
You still have nothing,
or else you would've
arrested me by now.

944
00:57:59,644 --> 00:58:03,180
Maybe, but I know what's
runnin' through your head
right now.

945
00:58:03,213 --> 00:58:05,650
Yeah? And what's that?

946
00:58:05,683 --> 00:58:08,252
You're asking yourself,
"How did he get that tape?

947
00:58:08,285 --> 00:58:10,821
And now that he's got it,
what's he gonna do with it?"

948
00:58:10,855 --> 00:58:14,258
[ Laughing ]
Let me tell you somethin'.

949
00:58:14,291 --> 00:58:16,927
I don't give a shit
where you got it,

950
00:58:16,961 --> 00:58:19,229
and you can
shove that shit
right up your ass,

951
00:58:19,263 --> 00:58:22,600
'cause I'm quite sure
that shit's not admissible.

952
00:58:22,633 --> 00:58:24,635
Maybe it is,
and maybe it isn't.

953
00:58:26,336 --> 00:58:29,874
But doesn't it bother you
that one of your crew
dropped a dime on you,

954
00:58:29,907 --> 00:58:33,310
that right now we're
working with one of you
to bring the rest of you down?

955
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:37,915
This tape, it may not be enough
to convict you by itself,

956
00:58:37,948 --> 00:58:40,851
but it's just the first piece
of evidence in a long line
of evidence to come.

957
00:58:45,055 --> 00:58:47,725
That's bullshit.

958
00:58:47,758 --> 00:58:49,994
How else would I
get it then?

959
00:58:50,027 --> 00:58:52,630
How else would I know
where you guys were
unless one of you told me?

960
00:58:55,099 --> 00:58:59,670
So, who was it then?
Uh-uh. That's for you
to find out.

961
00:58:59,704 --> 00:59:03,674
I got a hunch though.
I think you already know.

962
00:59:03,708 --> 00:59:05,676
[ Chuckling ]

963
00:59:24,328 --> 00:59:26,831
We're closed, fellas.

964
00:59:31,636 --> 00:59:34,338
So what's it gonna take
to reopen, huh?

965
00:59:34,371 --> 00:59:36,373
Not tonight.

966
00:59:36,406 --> 00:59:38,876
You gotta go, buddy.

967
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:42,647
Look, two shots of bourbon,
a little information,
we'll be on our way.

968
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:44,281
What do you say?

969
00:59:51,321 --> 00:59:53,290
[ Sighs ]
The shot I can do.

970
00:59:53,323 --> 00:59:58,362
If you want information,
dial 411.

971
00:59:58,395 --> 01:00:01,598
Maybe I'm not
makin' myself clear.

972
01:00:06,270 --> 01:00:09,239
I'm lookin' for four brothers
that are running things
out here.

973
01:00:09,273 --> 01:00:12,176
T-Mack, E-Bone,
Money and Simon.

974
01:00:12,209 --> 01:00:14,679
- Ring a bell?
- Never heard of 'em.

975
01:00:17,281 --> 01:00:20,651
And you're sure
about that?

976
01:00:22,720 --> 01:00:26,190
Yeah? Trust me, amigo,
you won't make it.

977
01:00:26,223 --> 01:00:28,325
Why don't you leave
your number?

978
01:00:29,794 --> 01:00:32,329
What, are you looking
for some action, baby? Hmm?

979
01:00:32,362 --> 01:00:34,865
You ain't got to call me.
I got a truck right outside.

980
01:00:34,899 --> 01:00:37,702
- Watch your
fuckin' mouth, Jack.
- Hey, fuck you, slim.

981
01:00:37,735 --> 01:00:41,005
- And don't be callin' me Jack.
- He didn't mean anything by it.

982
01:00:41,038 --> 01:00:43,808
Yeah? Well, I don't give a shit.
That happens to be my name.

983
01:00:43,841 --> 01:00:47,177
Besides, he doesn't know me
well enough to be
callin' me by name.

984
01:00:47,211 --> 01:00:50,380
You are real close
to crossin' that line.

985
01:00:50,414 --> 01:00:53,818
And it's obvious you guys
ain't from around here.

986
01:00:53,851 --> 01:00:56,420
So why don't you
put away your gun now?

987
01:00:56,453 --> 01:01:00,257
I'll take your number
and pass it on to someone
who might be able to help you.

988
01:01:00,290 --> 01:01:02,392
And forget the whole thing.

989
01:01:02,426 --> 01:01:05,696
If not, you're gonna
have a problem.

990
01:01:06,931 --> 01:01:08,799
Really? Yeah?

991
01:01:08,833 --> 01:01:10,801
You're scarin' me, baby.

992
01:01:10,835 --> 01:01:13,838
Well, it ain't me
you need to be worried about.

993
01:01:16,741 --> 01:01:19,043
All right, baby.

994
01:01:19,076 --> 01:01:21,812
Pedro, put it away.

995
01:01:25,049 --> 01:01:29,153
Vinnie, give these guys
another round on the house...

996
01:01:29,186 --> 01:01:32,189
and something to write with.

997
01:01:40,998 --> 01:01:43,100
I'm gonna be at this number
till the end of the week.

998
01:01:43,133 --> 01:01:45,435
After that, I'm gone.

999
01:01:45,469 --> 01:01:48,072
Where to?

1000
01:01:48,105 --> 01:01:50,040
To Miami.

1001
01:01:53,978 --> 01:01:57,181
- I'll see that they get it.
- Yeah, you do that.

1002
01:01:57,214 --> 01:01:59,984
'Cause it'll be worth
a whole lot of dough
to them if they do.

1003
01:02:00,017 --> 01:02:03,220
And I mean
a whole lot of dough.
For you too.

1004
01:02:03,253 --> 01:02:07,324
Hell, maybe you can even
buy this place
or a place like this.

1005
01:02:07,357 --> 01:02:09,760
You should think
about that. You know?

1006
01:02:18,302 --> 01:02:20,337
Thanks for the drink, Jack.

1007
01:02:32,582 --> 01:02:35,452
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

1008
01:02:35,485 --> 01:02:37,822
* Get on up
Get on up *

1009
01:02:37,855 --> 01:02:41,959
* She was about 5 foot 6
130 pounds *

1010
01:02:41,992 --> 01:02:45,429
* Thick in the right places
in a green nightgown *

1011
01:02:45,462 --> 01:02:49,800
* Can I touch your jazzmatazz
Keep sweat up
and we'll make it last *

1012
01:02:49,834 --> 01:02:52,002
* Forever

1013
01:02:52,036 --> 01:02:54,905
* Her essence warmed up the room
like the heat does in June *

1014
01:02:54,939 --> 01:02:57,975
* Can't wait to plant seeds
in that tripped-out lover *

1015
01:02:58,008 --> 01:02:59,977
* Hips like an ocean

1016
01:03:00,010 --> 01:03:02,980
Do you want another dance?

1017
01:03:03,013 --> 01:03:05,415
[ E-Bone ]
No, that's a'ight.
But that was good though.

1018
01:03:05,449 --> 01:03:07,251
* Lipstick and strawberries

1019
01:03:07,284 --> 01:03:09,353
Mmm. That's right.
* And me, I'm just

1020
01:03:09,386 --> 01:03:14,058
* An average-type fellow
Can we get jazzy *

1021
01:03:14,091 --> 01:03:15,826
* I wanna get jazzy

1022
01:03:17,561 --> 01:03:20,597
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]
Someone was lookin'
for you.

1023
01:03:20,630 --> 01:03:22,599
I don't know any "Jack."

1024
01:03:22,632 --> 01:03:25,202
He knows you.
Yeah? Well,

1025
01:03:25,235 --> 01:03:27,404
lots of motherfuckers
know me.

1026
01:03:27,437 --> 01:03:30,807
- That don't mean shit.
- He said it could mean
a lot of money for you.

1027
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:37,447
So, is that why
you came down here,
to bring me a proposition?

1028
01:03:37,481 --> 01:03:40,017
He said there would be
something in it for me,

1029
01:03:40,050 --> 01:03:42,286
and I got a eye
for business.

1030
01:03:42,319 --> 01:03:47,624
- What'd he look like?
- Thirty-somethin', Cuban.

1031
01:03:47,657 --> 01:03:49,994
But the number's only good
for 24 hours.

1032
01:03:50,027 --> 01:03:53,898
- What's the rush?
- He goes back
to the Sunshine State.

1033
01:03:53,931 --> 01:03:55,599
Miami.

1034
01:03:58,568 --> 01:04:01,505
You just can't admit it,
can you?

1035
01:04:01,538 --> 01:04:04,041
Admit what?

1036
01:04:04,074 --> 01:04:07,077
- The real reason you came here.
- The reason is in your hand.

1037
01:04:12,016 --> 01:04:15,152
I can see what kind
of position you're in here.

1038
01:04:15,185 --> 01:04:18,355
I mean, it's
a delicate situation--

1039
01:04:18,388 --> 01:04:23,127
you being who you are
and me bein' who I am.

1040
01:04:23,160 --> 01:04:25,462
But, dig,

1041
01:04:25,495 --> 01:04:27,965
I'm willin' to look
past all that to see you...

1042
01:04:27,998 --> 01:04:31,635
for who you really are
and what you really want.

1043
01:04:31,668 --> 01:04:33,603
Oh, of course.

1044
01:04:33,637 --> 01:04:36,273
And you're gonna give me
what I really want, right?

1045
01:04:36,306 --> 01:04:38,642
I aim to please.

1046
01:04:38,675 --> 01:04:40,945
So, are you gonna
do me right here?

1047
01:04:42,579 --> 01:04:44,681
[ Chuckles ]
Nah.

1048
01:04:44,714 --> 01:04:46,583
I got somewhere
to be now.

1049
01:04:49,553 --> 01:04:53,924
147 Lafayette Avenue.

1050
01:04:53,958 --> 01:04:56,393
I shouldn't be more
than an hour.
Make yourself at home.

1051
01:04:56,426 --> 01:05:00,230
You don't waste any time,
do you?
Look, my time is valuable.

1052
01:05:00,264 --> 01:05:03,067
Let's say I take those keys
and show them to Benny?

1053
01:05:03,100 --> 01:05:06,636
Then he'd be the one waiting
for you when you get home.

1054
01:05:06,670 --> 01:05:10,507
Like I said,
if you weren't interested,

1055
01:05:10,540 --> 01:05:12,642
you wouldn't be here.

1056
01:05:16,580 --> 01:05:19,416
I got some eggs
in the refrigerator.

1057
01:05:19,449 --> 01:05:21,285
I get a little hungry
late nights.

1058
01:05:28,358 --> 01:05:31,528
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]

1059
01:05:41,505 --> 01:05:43,507
So, what's up, man?

1060
01:05:43,540 --> 01:05:47,011
You in or you out?

1061
01:05:47,044 --> 01:05:49,079
What it look like?
I'm here, ain't I?

1062
01:05:49,113 --> 01:05:51,515
Yeah, but you ain't
sayin' much.

1063
01:05:51,548 --> 01:05:55,019
Like you nervous
or somethin'.

1064
01:05:55,052 --> 01:05:56,720
What the fuck
I got to be nervous about?

1065
01:05:56,753 --> 01:05:58,688
You tell me.

1066
01:06:01,225 --> 01:06:03,660
I ain't never nervous.

1067
01:06:03,693 --> 01:06:07,364
I thought we were supposed
to be here talkin' about
how to handle this Benny shit.

1068
01:06:07,397 --> 01:06:10,334
I don't think it's such
a good idea to talk about
that war shit right now.

1069
01:06:10,367 --> 01:06:13,003
Why not?

1070
01:06:13,037 --> 01:06:16,206
My people--
they scared of Benny, man.

1071
01:06:16,240 --> 01:06:18,175
I don't think
they'd go up against him.

1072
01:06:18,208 --> 01:06:20,510
[ Sighs ]

1073
01:06:21,811 --> 01:06:25,549
- What about you, big fella?
- My peeps are down.

1074
01:06:25,582 --> 01:06:29,086
If Simon and his squad rolls,
my people will roll.

1075
01:06:31,788 --> 01:06:34,458
Yeah, my cats is all ready
to do they thing too.

1076
01:06:36,693 --> 01:06:39,063
I'm just not sure
that this is the right time.

1077
01:06:40,397 --> 01:06:42,799
[ Inhaling ]
Might be the only time.

1078
01:06:42,832 --> 01:06:46,170
[ Simon ]
How do you know?
Maybe Tristan's wrong.

1079
01:06:46,203 --> 01:06:49,039
Maybe Benny ain't got shit
planned for us.

1080
01:06:50,774 --> 01:06:53,277
Is that right?
That's not what you said
the other day.

1081
01:06:53,310 --> 01:06:56,680
- That was then. This is now.
- Yeah, what happened
to change yo mind?

1082
01:06:56,713 --> 01:06:59,183
Ain't shit
changed my mind.

1083
01:06:59,216 --> 01:07:01,351
Somethin' happened.

1084
01:07:04,388 --> 01:07:06,323
I just had time to think.

1085
01:07:07,857 --> 01:07:10,294
Well, what you thinkin' about?
You scared of Benny too?

1086
01:07:14,264 --> 01:07:16,466
I can't believe you said
some shit like that!

1087
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:21,205
As long as we been cool,
when have I ever
been punked by anybody?

1088
01:07:21,238 --> 01:07:24,141
Ever?

1089
01:07:29,146 --> 01:07:31,348
- Never.
- A'ight then.

1090
01:07:33,117 --> 01:07:36,186
What about y'all?

1091
01:07:36,220 --> 01:07:38,422
Don't seem like none
of you motherfuckers
at this table...

1092
01:07:38,455 --> 01:07:41,125
are sure about
anything right now.

1093
01:07:41,158 --> 01:07:44,661
[ Simon ]
What about you, E?
You still down?

1094
01:07:44,694 --> 01:07:47,197
No, I ain't down.

1095
01:07:47,231 --> 01:07:49,566
I don't believe
this motherfucker.

1096
01:07:49,599 --> 01:07:52,102
That's right.
You better believe it,
motherfucker,

1097
01:07:52,136 --> 01:07:55,139
'cause I don't
trust your ass no more.

1098
01:07:55,172 --> 01:07:59,443
- You don't trust me?
- You the one talkin' about
walkin' out and shit.

1099
01:07:59,476 --> 01:08:02,412
What's your real angle,
Tristan?

1100
01:08:02,446 --> 01:08:05,115
[ Scoffs ]
What the fuck
is you talkin' about, man?

1101
01:08:05,149 --> 01:08:08,318
You know goddamn well
what I'm talkin' about,
motherfucker.

1102
01:08:08,352 --> 01:08:10,520
You tryin' to set us up.

1103
01:08:10,554 --> 01:08:13,357
- Motherfucker,
I oughta whup your ass!
- Man, fuck you!

1104
01:08:13,390 --> 01:08:16,626
Hey, look, man. Come on!
Hey! Hey! Come on, man!
Come out with your bullshit!

1105
01:08:16,660 --> 01:08:18,628
Why don't y'all motherfuckers
calm down, man!

1106
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:21,265
I'm tired of this motherfucker
always comin' at me
with this bullshit!

1107
01:08:21,298 --> 01:08:24,401
The truth hurts,
don't it?

1108
01:08:30,640 --> 01:08:33,243
[ Tristan ]
All y'all feel like this?

1109
01:08:34,444 --> 01:08:37,481
I don't know
what to think, man.

1110
01:08:37,514 --> 01:08:40,450
But your ass is actin'
funny and shit.

1111
01:08:42,319 --> 01:08:45,255
Oh, I'm actin' funny?
[ Chuckles ]

1112
01:08:51,828 --> 01:08:55,432
What about you, man?
You think I'm actin' funny too?

1113
01:09:00,904 --> 01:09:03,473
You too?

1114
01:09:05,409 --> 01:09:08,212
Then fuck it then!

1115
01:09:08,245 --> 01:09:10,547
Why don't y'all
just go the fuck ahead
